    {
      "id": "8fb06f45-6887-ef11-8474-000d3a37e3b6",
      "type": "GeneralText",
      "area": "General",
      "position": 1,
      "content": "The Ancient Near East and Egyptology major encompasses the study of early civilizations that inhabited the region that roughly corresponds to the modern Middle East, the field of Ancient Near East and Egyptology is one that is interdisciplinary and includes the study of the art and archaeology, history, language, literature, and religion relevant to that region. Listed below are the lower division preparation courses for the major. To be considered for admission to this major, you must complete the following courses by the end of spring before transfer: One civilization course on Mesopotamia, Egypt, Near Eastern Archeology or Middle Eastern cultures. If none of these courses are available, applicants must express sincere interest in this major. All courses must be taken for a letter grade. For more information regarding this major and UCLA's transfer selection process, visit: https:// nelc.ucla.edu and https:// admission.ucla . edu . PLEASE NOTE: the community college courses listed below have been approved to satisfy the preparation requirements for this major at UCLA, but they may not be exact equivalents of the UCLA courses listed.",
      "contentHtml": "<p>The Ancient Near East and Egyptology major encompasses the study of early civilizations that inhabited the region that roughly corresponds to the modern Middle East, the field of Ancient Near East and Egyptology is one that is interdisciplinary and includes the study of the art and archaeology, history, language, literature, and religion relevant to that region.&nbsp;</p><p><br></p><p>Listed below are the lower division preparation courses for the major.</p><p><br></p><p>To be considered for admission to this major, you must complete the following courses by the end of spring before transfer:</p><ul><li>One civilization course on Mesopotamia, Egypt, Near Eastern Archeology or Middle Eastern cultures.</li></ul><p>If none of these courses are available, applicants must express sincere interest in this major.</p><p>All courses must be taken for a letter grade.</p><p><br></p><p>For more information regarding this major and UCLA's transfer selection process, visit: <u style=\"color: rgb(41, 98, 255);\">https://</u><a href=\"http://www.nelc.ucla.edu \" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\"><u>nelc.ucla.edu</u></a> and <u style=\"color: rgb(41, 98, 255);\">https://</u><a href=\"http://www.admission.ucla\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">admission.ucla</a><a href=\"http://www.admission.ucla\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(41, 98, 255);\"><u>.</u></a><u style=\"color: rgb(41, 98, 255);\">edu</u>.</p><p><br></p><p>PLEASE NOTE: the community college courses listed below have been approved to satisfy the preparation requirements for this major at UCLA, but they may not be exact equivalents of the UCLA courses listed.</p>"
    },
